{
  "texts": [
    "F satisfies both (a) R-down -if xR i y and y ′ ⊑ y, then xR i y ′ (recall Figure 2.2); (b) R-dense -xR i y if ∀y ′ ⊑ y ∃y ′′ ⊑ y ′: xR i y ′′ (see Figure 2.8).Proof.",
    "R-down corresponds to persistence of R i (x) and R-dense corresponds to refinability of R i (x).Note how the conditions above relate to the up-R condition from intuitionistic frames (Example 2.7).Fact 2.33 (Deriving up-R).",
    "For any partial-state frame F, if F satisfies R-rule, R-down, and R-dense, then F satisfies up-R.Proof.",
    "To show that x ′ ⊑ x and x ′ R i y together imply xR i y, suppose x ′ ⊑ x but y ̸ ∈ R i (x).",
    "Then by R-dense, there is a y ′ ⊑ y such that (i) for all y ′′ ⊑ y ′, y ′′ ̸ ∈ R i (x)."
  ]
}